WEBVTT

01:34.844 --> 01:37.931
Domain Expansion. Deadly Sentencing.

01:39.015 --> 01:42.769
<i>Before he can activate
his domain technique…</i>

01:43.269 --> 01:44.187
<i>I'll take him down!</i>

01:54.739 --> 01:58.867
In here, all violent acts are forbidden.

01:58.868 --> 02:00.577
For both of us.

02:00.578 --> 02:01.538
Both of us?

02:05.959 --> 02:09.295
Yes. Sorry. Verbal violence doesn't count.

02:10.421 --> 02:12.882
Judgeman, begin.

02:16.553 --> 02:18.804
Yuji Itadori,

02:18.805 --> 02:21.765
despite being under 18,

02:21.766 --> 02:25.144
on July 16th, 2017,

02:25.145 --> 02:29.273
you allegedly entered Maji Vegas,
a pachinko parlor in Sendai, Miyagi,

02:29.274 --> 02:32.068
as a customer.

02:34.612 --> 02:35.697
What?

02:36.281 --> 02:39.700
Uh… um… like…

02:39.701 --> 02:43.537
Judgeman knows everything
about everyone in this domain.

02:43.538 --> 02:44.580
UMM…
HMM…

02:44.581 --> 02:46.582
But don't worry.

02:46.583 --> 02:49.043
I don't get that information.

02:49.711 --> 02:53.715
The verdict is based only
on our two arguments.

02:55.049 --> 02:57.302
Except for this evidence.

02:59.387 --> 03:00.513
When did you…?

03:01.097 --> 03:04.517
This is the evidence Judgeman submitted.

03:05.101 --> 03:09.022
This evidence
doesn't necessarily prove you're guilty.

03:09.814 --> 03:12.275
I'm not telling you what it says.

03:12.859 --> 03:16.862
Now, you'll give your side,
clear the suspicion,

03:16.863 --> 03:19.908
and win a not-guilty verdict
from Judgeman.

03:21.659 --> 03:23.745
<i>A technique in the form of a trial…</i>

03:25.872 --> 03:28.750
<i>That badge… So he really is a lawyer?</i>

03:29.417 --> 03:31.836
<i>But this feels more like prosecution.</i>

03:33.254 --> 03:35.255
<i>Higuruma is a modern sorcerer,</i>

03:35.256 --> 03:37.675
<i>but this domain is what Tengen meant…</i>

03:39.135 --> 03:41.595
Domains used to be standard tech

03:41.596 --> 03:45.391
for old-school sorcerers.

03:46.434 --> 03:51.188
The reason is that older domains often

03:51.189 --> 03:54.358
left out the sure-kill part.

03:54.359 --> 03:55.275
SURE-HIT

03:55.276 --> 03:59.822
They force your technique
onto the target, a sure-hit.

04:00.990 --> 04:04.619
<i>That was the common domain back then.</i>

04:05.536 --> 04:08.497
People obsessed over sure-kill,

04:08.498 --> 04:11.083
so the requirements got harsher,

04:11.084 --> 04:14.170
domains became more advanced,

04:14.671 --> 04:17.006
and fewer people could use them.

04:17.924 --> 04:21.301
<i>So this domain isn't sure-kill.</i>

04:21.302 --> 04:23.971
<i>It can't physically hurt me,</i>

04:23.972 --> 04:27.266
<i>and it explains the rules to some extent.</i>

04:27.267 --> 04:28.893
<i>A binding vow that makes it work.</i>

04:31.145 --> 04:34.983
You get one chance to testify.
Same for me.

04:35.817 --> 04:38.735
After you, I'll respond once,

04:38.736 --> 04:40.321
based on the evidence,

04:40.947 --> 04:44.074
then Judgeman will deliver a verdict

04:44.075 --> 04:45.618
under the Six Codes.

04:46.995 --> 04:48.454
What happens if I'm found guilty?

04:49.455 --> 04:53.458
Unfortunately, I'm not obligated
to explain that.

04:53.459 --> 04:56.963
But I'll tell you this much,
as compensation.

04:58.214 --> 05:00.049
You've got three options.

05:00.633 --> 05:03.386
Silence. Confession. Denial.

05:04.012 --> 05:06.931
And denial includes lying.

05:08.016 --> 05:11.311
So it's okay to lie? In a trial?

05:12.145 --> 05:13.938
If everyone told the truth,

05:14.522 --> 05:16.607
we wouldn't need trials.

05:18.109 --> 05:20.194
All right. Make your excuse.

05:20.862 --> 05:22.947
Judgeman is not patient.

05:25.575 --> 05:28.243
<i>I did go to that pachinko place.</i>

05:28.244 --> 05:31.205
<i>I played, and I might have even won…</i>

05:31.831 --> 05:35.542
<i>To claim not guilty, I've got to lie.</i>

05:35.543 --> 05:38.337
<i>So I need to figure out</i>

05:38.921 --> 05:40.465
<i>what that evidence actually is…</i>

05:41.841 --> 05:45.887
This evidence doesn't necessarily
prove you're guilty.

05:47.430 --> 05:51.767
<i>Option one. If the evidence doesn't say
that I entered at all,</i>

05:51.768 --> 05:53.436
<i>I can stay silent or deny it.</i>

05:54.187 --> 05:55.395
<i>-No.
- Option two.</i>

05:55.396 --> 05:58.106
<i>If it only proves I entered,</i>

05:58.107 --> 06:00.400
<i>I can try an excuse
that leaves room for leniency.</i>

06:00.401 --> 06:02.694
<i>Like, I just needed the toilet.</i>

06:02.695 --> 06:04.488
<i>-But if it's option one…
- You entered, right?</i>

06:04.489 --> 06:06.573
<i>-That would be digging my own grave.
- Ye… Yes!</i>

06:06.574 --> 06:08.409
<i>Because I would be admitting I entered it.</i>

06:08.910 --> 06:12.120
<i>Option three.
If it proves I didn't just enter,</i>

06:12.121 --> 06:16.041
<i>but actually played,
I'm basically screwed.</i>

06:16.042 --> 06:17.459
<i>I regret it…</i>

06:17.460 --> 06:20.462
<i>Then I would have to confess
and hope the verdict is lighter…</i>

06:20.463 --> 06:23.466
<i>Does this trial even measure severity?</i>

06:25.176 --> 06:26.219
I…

06:27.053 --> 06:29.806
entered the pachinko parlor, Maji Vegas,

06:30.556 --> 06:33.976
but I only used the toilet
because I had an emergency.

06:35.436 --> 06:36.479
I see…

06:37.063 --> 06:38.730
<i>I'm ditching option three.</i>

06:38.731 --> 06:41.734
<i>No clue if leniency applies,</i>

06:42.360 --> 06:44.569
<i>but this sounds like the best impression…</i>

06:44.570 --> 06:46.196
<i>I think…</i>

06:46.197 --> 06:49.242
Then it's my turn.

06:53.079 --> 06:54.621
This is from the day of the incident

06:54.622 --> 06:57.667
- from a second-hand shop near Maji Vegas.
- What?

06:58.459 --> 07:02.130
To be blunt, it is a security cam photo
from the cash-out booth.

07:06.592 --> 07:08.343
The facial features, the build…

07:08.344 --> 07:11.556
May we assume that's you, Yuji Itadori?

07:15.852 --> 07:17.478
Now that you've admitted to entering,

07:18.104 --> 07:19.689
and looking at this photo,

07:20.440 --> 07:23.401
your toilet excuse isn't believable.

07:24.110 --> 07:27.112
So you likely entered to play,

07:27.113 --> 07:29.532
despite being under the age of 18.

07:31.242 --> 07:34.245
So what… What crime is that?

07:35.246 --> 07:36.746
The shop

07:36.747 --> 07:39.792
explicitly bans people
under the age of 18,

07:40.460 --> 07:42.420
so it's unlawful entry.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.964
Penal Code Article 130.

07:45.673 --> 07:49.135
Under the Entertainment Business Act,
minors aren't punished directly.

07:50.928 --> 07:52.929
That's cheating.

07:52.930 --> 07:55.390
No matter what I say, it doesn't matter.

07:55.391 --> 07:57.142
<i>So, it was option three?</i>

07:57.143 --> 07:59.186
What are you talking about?

07:59.187 --> 08:01.438
In Japan, gambling is illegal,

08:01.439 --> 08:04.066
so the shop and cash-out booth
are separate legal entities.

08:04.650 --> 08:07.611
Sometimes multiple shops share one.

08:07.612 --> 08:09.488
And what's being asked here is only

08:09.489 --> 08:12.033
whether you entered Maji Vegas.

08:12.533 --> 08:16.119
All you had to do was say,
"I don't know that place,"

08:16.120 --> 08:18.956
and deny the allegation.

08:20.166 --> 08:22.335
No, wait. We aren't at the verdict yet.

08:34.889 --> 08:36.557
<i>We're back in the real world…</i>

08:37.308 --> 08:39.643
<i>So, I'm guilty,</i>

08:39.644 --> 08:40.978
<i>but nothing has change--</i>

08:50.154 --> 08:51.030
<i>What's this?</i>

08:55.868 --> 08:57.078
<i>This gavel…</i>

08:57.578 --> 08:59.955
<i>He can summon it
and dismiss it whenever he wants,</i>

08:59.956 --> 09:01.832
<i>and even change its size.</i>

09:02.500 --> 09:03.876
<i>But more importantly…</i>

09:05.211 --> 09:06.462
He's tough.

09:07.213 --> 09:09.048
That's kind of my thing.

09:13.803 --> 09:15.388
<i>I can't knead my cursed energy!</i>

09:18.516 --> 09:20.601
<i>59th Training Class.</i>

09:21.227 --> 09:23.270
<i>Hiromi Higuruma, age 36,</i>

09:23.271 --> 09:26.232
<i>affiliated with the Iwate Bar Association.</i>

09:26.732 --> 09:27.732
CIVIL, CRIMINAL-CLASSIFICATION, YOU, ALL
HIGH, MED, LOW ACCURACY RATE QUESTIONS

09:27.733 --> 09:30.068
<i>He applied
to the Faculty of Law at T University.</i>

09:30.069 --> 09:33.738
<i>He passed every major hurdle
in a single attempt,</i>

09:33.739 --> 09:36.409
<i>including the old bar exam before
the law school system was introduced.</i>

09:37.618 --> 09:39.536
<i>To Higuruma, it was simple.</i>

09:39.537 --> 09:42.038
<i>Input whatever knowledge is needed,</i>

09:42.039 --> 09:46.002
<i>output what is needed.</i>

09:47.336 --> 09:48.629
<i>"A genius,"</i>

09:49.422 --> 09:51.923
<i>those who knew him whispered.</i>

09:51.924 --> 09:52.841
HIGURUMA LAW OFFICE

09:52.842 --> 09:56.970
<i>But his brightest raw talent</i>

09:56.971 --> 10:00.057
<i>was as a jujutsu sorcerer.</i>

10:02.393 --> 10:07.355
<i>With a domain built in by default,
he analyzed his own technique</i>

10:07.356 --> 10:10.318
<i>and, along the way,
mastered barrier techniques too.</i>

10:12.320 --> 10:14.946
<i>By working backwards
from barrier techniques,</i>

10:14.947 --> 10:18.325
<i>he got a feel for reinforcement
through cursed energy control,</i>

10:18.326 --> 10:20.785
<i>and within 12 days of awakening,</i>

10:20.786 --> 10:22.912
<i>he grew to a level comparable</i>

10:22.913 --> 10:25.374
<i>to a Grade One sorcerer.</i>

10:26.250 --> 10:30.253
<i>Before entering the colony,
he had exorcised countless curses,</i>

10:30.254 --> 10:32.881
<i>and even defeated</i>

10:32.882 --> 10:35.468
<i>over 20 players.</i>

11:13.381 --> 11:15.841
So you can't knead cursed energy now?

11:17.176 --> 11:18.719
You did this, didn't you?

11:20.346 --> 11:23.556
Confiscation temporarily disables

11:23.557 --> 11:25.351
the use of a technique.

11:25.976 --> 11:29.355
From what I can tell,
you didn't have one to begin with.

11:30.314 --> 11:34.360
So the penalty probably shifted
to "No cursed energy use."

11:35.778 --> 11:37.570
Also, confiscation is normally

11:37.571 --> 11:40.866
used as an additional penalty
and never imposed on its own.

11:41.992 --> 11:44.412
<i>It's terrifying, saying it out loud.</i>

11:45.538 --> 11:48.541
<i>How are you keeping up with me
without cursed energy?</i>

11:50.000 --> 11:53.003
<i>Is it not his sorcery,
but his innate physical body?</i>

11:53.504 --> 11:56.298
<i>As a living creature,
could his durability be insanely high?</i>

11:57.299 --> 12:00.343
<i>Most sorcerers,
after they lose their technique,</i>

12:00.344 --> 12:03.305
<i>their basic control gets sloppy.</i>

12:04.056 --> 12:05.891
<i>Maybe the years dulled their instincts.</i>

12:06.600 --> 12:10.062
<i>But his situation is worse.
He has a total cursed energy shutdown.</i>

12:10.938 --> 12:13.691
<i>And he's still fighting this well.</i>

12:14.400 --> 12:18.612
<i>Most people would've lost
to the first blow.</i>

12:19.822 --> 12:21.907
<i>If I slip up, I'll get caught.</i>

12:23.075 --> 12:24.452
<i>I'll crush him with everything…</i>

13:05.826 --> 13:06.619
You're incredible.

13:07.453 --> 13:10.331
<i>It's like I'm fighting
an unbreakable doll…</i>

13:11.081 --> 13:14.542
<i>Oh, no! How long is this going to last?</i>

13:14.543 --> 13:16.670
<i>Hurry up! Cursed energy, come on!</i>

13:17.713 --> 13:19.840
<i>He's got this much power, so…</i>

13:20.341 --> 13:23.093
<i>There has to be some condition
that puts him at a disadvantage, right?</i>

13:24.803 --> 13:27.056
<i>Think.</i>

13:28.349 --> 13:31.185
<i>A trial technique… A trial…</i>

13:39.151 --> 13:42.530
Higuruma! I want a retrial! One more time!

13:52.540 --> 13:53.958
You figured it out.

13:56.585 --> 13:58.002
That was close.

13:58.003 --> 14:00.422
A second trial, right?

14:01.674 --> 14:04.467
<i>Anyone found guilty by Judgeman</i>

14:04.468 --> 14:07.095
<i>and penalized</i>

14:07.096 --> 14:09.138
<i>can demand a retrial up to twice,</i>

14:09.139 --> 14:13.394
<i>as long as they don't admit guilt.</i>

14:14.019 --> 14:17.398
<i>Judgeman will never refuse.</i>

14:19.942 --> 14:21.944
Do it over! One more time!

14:25.155 --> 14:27.323
Yuji Itadori is suspected

14:27.324 --> 14:30.743
of mass murder in Shibuya

14:30.744 --> 14:34.748
on October 31st, 2018.

14:38.085 --> 14:40.129
Yes. I killed them.

14:40.713 --> 14:42.339
This is not a lie or a denial.

14:55.394 --> 14:56.478
<i>Higuruma.</i>

15:02.860 --> 15:04.028
Mr. Yoshizawa.

15:04.987 --> 15:08.032
If it's the draft, I submitted it earlier…

15:09.867 --> 15:11.493
No, not that.

15:12.161 --> 15:14.747
I read it. It's excellent.

15:15.497 --> 15:18.459
Honestly, it could be used
as the verdict as-is.

15:20.294 --> 15:24.506
You said you wanted to be
a prosecutor or a defense lawyer, right?

15:25.466 --> 15:26.342
Yes.

15:27.051 --> 15:28.052
How about this?

15:29.803 --> 15:32.181
Why don't you aim to become a judge?

15:41.899 --> 15:45.277
<i>The heaviest sentence Judgeman can impose.</i>

15:46.028 --> 15:49.864
<i>Death penalty with confiscation.</i>

15:49.865 --> 15:50.699
SWORD OF EXECUTIONER

15:52.076 --> 15:55.286
<i>With confiscation, the technique,</i>

15:55.287 --> 15:56.663
<i>or in Itadori's case,</i>

15:56.664 --> 15:59.874
<i>his cursed energy is disabled.</i>

15:59.875 --> 16:03.462
<i>And Higuruma receives
the Sword of the Executioner.</i>

16:04.713 --> 16:08.383
<i>Anyone cut by that sword</i>

16:08.384 --> 16:09.843
<i>will die</i>

16:10.469 --> 16:12.221
<i>without exception.</i>

16:13.389 --> 16:15.974
<i>To stand beside someone's heart</i>

16:15.975 --> 16:18.936
<i>means understanding their weakness.</i>

16:19.812 --> 16:23.065
<i>The victim's weakness.
The offender's weakness.</i>

16:24.566 --> 16:27.361
<i>Day after day after day…</i>

16:28.404 --> 16:30.155
<i>I grew sick of it.</i>

16:31.573 --> 16:35.034
<i>Ugly. The more I interacted with people,</i>

16:35.035 --> 16:37.371
<i>the more I began to think so.</i>

16:38.372 --> 16:40.124
You're the same Itadori!

16:42.459 --> 16:45.462
People are all weak and ugly!

16:46.255 --> 16:49.258
No matter how noble a soul you wish for,

16:52.469 --> 16:54.595
there's nothing that awaits!

16:54.596 --> 16:56.724
Beyond darkness,
there is just more darkness!

16:58.308 --> 16:59.893
<i>Even if you light a lamp,</i>

17:00.561 --> 17:03.564
another blinding void spreads beyond!

17:09.611 --> 17:10.696
I'm sorry.

17:11.280 --> 17:13.699
I won't become a judge.

17:18.662 --> 17:21.957
<i>I see. Can I at least ask why?</i>

17:23.250 --> 17:26.253
People are all weak and ugly.

17:28.839 --> 17:32.468
<i>It doesn't suit someone like me
who has no interest in being promoted.</i>

17:33.552 --> 17:36.637
<i>But back then…</i>

17:36.638 --> 17:38.474
<i>At least until that time…</i>

17:39.266 --> 17:42.351
<i>I believed that impurity,
unique to humans,</i>

17:42.352 --> 17:44.605
<i>was something that deserved reverence!</i>

17:45.689 --> 17:47.273
<i>Why?</i>

17:47.274 --> 17:48.400
<i>Yuji Itadori…</i>

17:49.485 --> 17:51.195
<i>Why did you admit your guilt?</i>

17:51.820 --> 17:55.156
<i>The contents of the evidence
submitted by Judgeman</i>

17:55.157 --> 17:58.869
<i>are shared with the sorcerer
even before they're opened.</i>

17:59.578 --> 18:01.079
<i>The evidence concerns the devil</i>

18:01.080 --> 18:04.249
<i>dwelling inside you, which is Sukuna!</i>

18:05.751 --> 18:06.710
<i>You didn't kill them!</i>

18:08.128 --> 18:10.089
<i>Why?</i>

18:32.444 --> 18:35.405
Article 39, Paragraph 1.

18:36.824 --> 18:39.409
If either the capacity to discern

18:40.160 --> 18:43.247
or the capacity for control is absent,
the defendant is deemed legally insane.

18:45.290 --> 18:49.585
In Shibuya, your body
was possessed by Sukuna.

18:49.586 --> 18:51.338
How do you know about Sukuna?

18:52.381 --> 18:54.925
In other words, you had no control.

18:55.509 --> 18:59.387
You also didn't voluntarily
abandon that control.

18:59.388 --> 19:00.264
Which means…

19:01.223 --> 19:02.141
you're not guilty.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.270
You bear no crime.

19:08.605 --> 19:11.066
But still, it's my fault.

19:12.526 --> 19:14.069
Because I was too weak.

19:18.282 --> 19:19.408
I see.

19:20.492 --> 19:21.451
Higuruma…

19:22.119 --> 19:24.163
Why did you release your technique?

19:28.041 --> 19:29.960
I returned to my starting point.

19:31.920 --> 19:32.880
Itadori,

19:33.380 --> 19:36.425
there may still be others

19:37.009 --> 19:38.886
who carry weakness like yours.

19:40.721 --> 19:44.683
Put your clothes on. Then sit.
I'll give you 100 points.

19:58.697 --> 19:59.740
Itadori.

20:01.283 --> 20:04.453
Have you ever killed someone
by your own will?

20:12.294 --> 20:13.253
I have.

20:19.176 --> 20:20.010
I see.

20:22.387 --> 20:24.348
<i>It must have felt terrible.</i>

21:56.023 --> 21:58.233
Kogane, add a new rule.

21:59.359 --> 22:02.988
Allow players to transfer points
between each other.

22:03.947 --> 22:08.285
Of course,
this falls under Rule Eight, "Adjustment."

22:08.910 --> 22:10.370
Approved.

22:10.996 --> 22:17.127
<i>Rule Ten. A player may transfer
any number of points to another player.</i>

22:18.795 --> 22:21.548
Kogane, transfer one point to Itadori.

22:22.215 --> 22:23.675
Understood.

22:25.844 --> 22:29.139
One point has been transferred
from Hiromi Higuruma.

22:30.390 --> 22:34.603
For 19 days from now, neither of us
can have our techniques stripped.

22:35.520 --> 22:36.605
Take care.

22:37.439 --> 22:40.192
Higuruma… What are you going to do now?

22:40.776 --> 22:43.779
If you're willing, would you help us?

22:45.864 --> 22:47.239
The remaining two points

22:47.240 --> 22:49.784
<i>belonged to the judge
and prosecutor I killed</i>

22:49.785 --> 22:51.661
<i>before coming to Tokyo.</i>

22:53.080 --> 22:54.872
When the barrier opens,

22:54.873 --> 22:56.416
maybe I'll turn myself in.

22:57.542 --> 23:00.629
Until then,
I'll think about what I should do.

23:01.546 --> 23:06.051
Besides, being around you
makes me hate myself even more.

23:07.427 --> 23:10.305
I'm sorry. I wasn't blaming you.

23:12.015 --> 23:13.016
See you.

23:21.691 --> 23:23.359
A new rule will be added soon.

23:23.360 --> 23:25.986
Players may transfer
any number of points at will.

23:25.987 --> 23:27.780
<i>If you’re going to do it,
come at us ready to kill.</i>

23:27.781 --> 23:30.157
You’re sure about that?
For the rest of your life… Wi-fi!

23:30.158 --> 23:32.952
<i>Hand over all your points.</i>

23:32.953 --> 23:35.872
NEXT EPISODE
